'''''Navya Nair''''' (born ) whose real name is '''Dhanya Nair''', is a  actress. Trained in dance, Navya has been  whooping up at youth festivals and stage shows. She has won the honour of Kala  in the youth festival of Aleppey district, Kerala for her  talent.  With her first movie ‘Ishtam’ opposite  she attained winning the hearts  . She stepped to Tamil film through 'Azhagiya Theeyee' which made  impact in the minds of Tamil audience also. She is noted for her portrayal of the typical ''Malayali'' () girl in various movies. She debuted in the Malayalam film ''Ishtam'' (2001). She bagged the Kerala State Award for the Best Actress in 2002 for the film ''Nandanam''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2003/12/04/stories/2003120404870400.htm|work=The Hindu|title=State film awards presented|date=2003-12-04|accessdate=2007-05-26}}</ref> and again in 2005 for her performance in films ''Kanne Madanguka'' and ''Saira''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/02/08/stories/2006020808150600.htm|work=The Hindu|title=Kerala State film awards for 2005 announced|date=2006-02-08|accessdate=2007-05-26}}</ref>